<br>
At first I just hunted the two magicians in the crystal room.  I used the water pet for damage and better damage mitigation.  I fully buffed it, {Best armor, focus items, weapons, shield, etc.}  <br>
<br>
It is tough to break the room with both magicians and thier pets up, but once broken, it is easy to hold.  The magicians are on a fixed spawn time and it is safe to med in that room.  The only danger is a orge guard will come to the entrance to the room.  If you are medding near the entrance to the room,  it will attack you.  I always medded in the corner facing the entrance and stood while he was at the entrance to the room.  He can also be killed, but is often green and there is no need. <br>
<br>
After you split the magicans spawns a little, you will quickly get back to full mana in a spawn cycle or two.  I added the dark-bone skeleton that you could aggro by going out on the ledge near the hallway leading to this room.  <br>
<br>
I stayed here from 24/25th till 31st level.  There are four dark-bone skeletons you can safely pull one at a time, just have to look out for the wandering guard.  They drop good loot and are good EP for their level.  As you gain levels, you can take more of the Dark-bone skeletons in a spawn cycle and maintain the rate that you get ep.  <br>
<br>
I entered Najena a poor under-equipped magician.  I left Najena with all my focus items, all my spells {went back and bought all the ones I had to pass on because I was to poor}, the four pages for my epic, a couple of Magic items I picked up in East Commons before the bazaar killed it,  and money in the bank.  <br>
<br>
<br>
