<br>
I got all 4 around 24th lvl, and noticed a big difference. I most often used focused fire at 24th. The difference was hefty. Although I do not have any parses, let me just describe it. <br>
<br>
With unfocused fire, I would camp the millers in QH, and breaking the spawn got hairy. The pet would barely make it, or sometimes didn't and had to be chained! I would often use several bubs of mana, and I have a lot. With Focused fire pets, the break was fairly simple, the pet had more hit points, and seemed to mitigate damage better. I would burn on Chandra, and then a single shock or 2 for Baoslob, and he was running like a sissy. Downtime was significantly decreased, and I found myself sitting, waiting for respawn... so much, that I went to Marus Seru for the constant pulls I could make with KEI.<br>
<br>
I had my first focus in my teens. It was the Water focus, and it made a big difference then too! <p>      <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Love is the answer; but while you're waiting for the answer, sex raises some pretty good questions.&quot; (Woody Allen) </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elfnom>Elfnom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 5:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Items</span><hr size=1> <br>
